x4freetext: Absolute differential   cross   sections   for    the

berillium  have  been  measured  using  the   oxford
110-MeV synchrotron.  A proton telescope was used to
select protons of energy 37 MeV,  47 MeV, 55 MeV, 63
MeV,  and  78  MeV,  using bremsstrahlung beams with
end-point  energies  from  40  MeV   to   110   MeV.
